<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="035" project="spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>PCF build + deploy via `/pcf-deploy` (NFR-10 clean-rebuild)</title>
    <phase>D: PCF v1.1.74 (Deploy)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>1-2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>034</dependencies>
    <blocks>040, 072</blocks>
    <tags>pcf, deploy, dataverse</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Mechanical deploy task following `/pcf-deploy` skill verbatim. Explicit NFR-10 + saved-lesson constraint. No source-code logic; not vague docs.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Deploy gate — must follow tests-green (034) and precede Phase E start (040 depends on PCF deployed first).</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Deploy PCF v1.1.74 via the `/pcf-deploy` skill. CRITICAL pre-step: clean-rebuild `@spaarke/auth` and `@spaarke/ui-components` `dist/` BEFORE the PCF build (NFR-10 — per saved lesson `feedback_stale-shared-lib-dist-poisons-codepage-bundle`). Then `npm run build:prod`, pack solution via `pack.ps1`, import ZIP via PAC. Verify deployed PCF footer shows v1.1.74 and the deploy log includes the clean-rebuild evidence.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    PCF deployer with familiarity with the `/pcf-deploy` skill verbatim. The clean-rebuild step is non-negotiable: stale shared-lib `dist/` has been observed to poison PCF + code-page bundles, causing subtle runtime bugs (saved lesson `feedback_stale-shared-lib-dist-poisons-codepage-bundle`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Deployed PCF on the test environment shows footer `v1.1.74`; deploy log shows the clean-rebuild of `@spaarke/auth` + `@spaarke/ui-components` happened BEFORE the PCF build; solution ZIP imports cleanly with no Dataverse warnings. Downstream Phase E (tasks 040+) can take a dependency on the PCF being live.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      `/pcf-deploy` is the canonical skill for PCF deploys; it embeds the 5-location version check (already done in 033), the production-mode build, the clean-rebuild of shared libs (NFR-10), and the PAC solution import. Saved lesson `feedback_stale-shared-lib-dist-poisons-codepage-bundle` documents the failure mode the clean-rebuild prevents.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/spaarke-auth/</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-10">PCF deploy MUST follow `/pcf-deploy` skill exactly — including 5-location version bump (done in 033), production-mode build, and clean-rebuild of `@spaarke/auth` + `@spaarke/ui-components` `dist/` BEFORE the PCF build.</constraint>
    <constraint source="saved lesson `feedback_stale-shared-lib-dist-poisons-codepage-bundle`">Mandatory clean rebuild of `@spaarke/auth` + `@spaarke/ui-components` `dist/` before PCF build. Stale `dist/` has been observed to cause subtle runtime bugs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="saved lesson `feedback_deploy-asks-follow-skill-no-openended-questions`">Invoke the deploy skill verbatim; hand over file paths; no open-ended questions.</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md">Use `npm run build:prod` (production mode); pack via `pack.ps1`; import via PAC.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-03">Production bundle ≤ 1 MB (already verified in 033; revalidate).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/PCF-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Pre-PCF-build clean-rebuild of shared libs" location="saved lesson `feedback_stale-shared-lib-dist-poisons-codepage-bundle`">
        Before `npm run build:prod` in the PCF, run `npm run build` (clean) in `@spaarke/auth` and `@spaarke/ui-components` to refresh their `dist/`. The PCF bundle consumes the `dist/` artifacts; stale `dist/` produces stale bundles.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Clean + rebuild `@spaarke/auth` `dist/`: in `src/client/shared/spaarke-auth/` (or the canonical path per the workspace), delete the existing `dist/` and run `npm run build`. Verify the output is fresh.</step>
    <step order="2">Clean + rebuild `@spaarke/ui-components` `dist/`: in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/`, delete the existing `dist/` and run `npm run build`. Verify the output is fresh.</step>
    <step order="3">In `src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/`, run `npm run build:prod`. Verify production bundle is ≤ 1 MB (NFR-03 re-check).</step>
    <step order="4">Pack the PCF solution via `Solution/pack.ps1` — produces `bin/Release/Sprk_SemanticSearchControl_1_1_74.zip` (or equivalent).</step>
    <step order="5">Import the solution ZIP via PAC CLI: `pac solution import --path {zip}`. Capture import log.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify the deployed PCF on the test environment: open a model-driven form hosting SemanticSearchControl; confirm footer shows `v1.1.74 • Built YYYY-MM-DD`.</step>
    <step order="7">Capture the full deploy log (clean-rebuild evidence + build output + import result + footer screenshot) in `projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/handoffs/035-pcf-deploy.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Bash">Run npm + pack + PAC commands</tool>
    <tool name="Read">Read deploy logs + verify version files</tool>
    <tool name="Skill">Invoke `pcf-deploy` skill for the full deploy sequence</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="artifact">PCF solution ZIP (v1.1.74) imported to test environment</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/handoffs/035-pcf-deploy.md (deploy log evidence)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">NFR-10: Deploy log shows clean-rebuild of `@spaarke/auth` + `@spaarke/ui-components` `dist/` happened BEFORE the PCF build. Verified by handoff notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PCF solution ZIP imports cleanly via PAC — no Dataverse warnings or errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Deployed PCF footer shows `v1.1.74 • Built YYYY-MM-DD` on the test environment.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NFR-03: Production bundle measured ≤ 1 MB. Re-verified in this task.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Deployed PCF version visible">
      <description>Smoke check that the deployed PCF on the test environment is the v1.1.74 build.</description>
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=entityrecord&amp;etn={entity}&amp;id={record-id}</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open a model-driven form hosting SemanticSearchControl on the test environment.</step>
        <step>Locate the footer of the PCF control.</step>
        <step>Open browser DevTools → Console to check for any load errors.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Footer reads `v1.1.74 • Built YYYY-MM-DD`. No console errors. Control mounts and renders interactively.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    The clean-rebuild step is the single most important guardrail in this task. Skipping it has caused production bugs in past deploys (saved lesson). Even if `dist/` "looks fresh", rebuild it.

    If the PCF import fails, the most common root causes are (a) version mismatch across the 5 locations from task 033 — recheck; (b) Dataverse environment cache — try `pac solution import --force-overwrite` per the skill docs; (c) shared-lib `dist/` not actually refreshed — verify file mtimes.

    Downstream task 040 (code-page types extension) starts AFTER this deploy completes successfully. Phase H deploy ordering: A.5 → B → A → D (this) → E → F.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>
      Load .claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md verbatim. Declare rigor (STANDARD) per task-execute Step 0. Invoke `pcf-deploy` skill for the deploy steps.
    </protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
